ssor-contract statute requires subcontractor engagement to be by written contract imposing equivalent obligations.","id":"USDPA-018-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Processor shall engage any subcontractor only pursuant to a written contract requiring the subcontractor to meet the obligations of Processor under this Agreement.'","rule_id":"USDPA-018","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-va-code-59-1-579-colo-rev-stat-6-1-1305-similar","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Va. Code § 59.1-579 / Colo. Rev. Stat. § 6-1-1305 / similar","source_url":"https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacodefull/title59.1/chapter53/"}],"title":"Subcontractor written-contract clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found requiring the processor to provide information demonstrating compliance.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Most state privacy statutes require the processor to make information available demonstrating compliance.","id":"USDPA-019-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Processor shall make available to Controller information necessary to demonstrate compliance with this Agreement and applicable state privacy law.'","rule_id":"USDPA-019","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-va-code-59-1-579-colo-rev-stat-6-1-1305-similar","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Va. Code § 59.1-579 / Colo. Rev. Stat. § 6-1-1305 / similar","source_url":"https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacodefull/title59.1/chapter53/"}],"title":"Compliance-demonstration clause missing"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a governing-law clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no governing-law clause)"},"explanation":"A governing-law clause picks the legal system that interprets the contract. Without it, courts apply conflict-of-laws rules, which may produce unexpected results.","id":"CHOICE-001-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No governing-law clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not allocate ownership of intellectual property.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no IP-ownership clause)"},"explanation":"Without an IP-ownership clause, default copyright and patent rules apply: under 17 U.S.C. § 201, copyright vests in the author/employee unless work-for-hire or assignment applies.","id":"IPDATA-001-s1-0","rule_id":"IPDATA-001","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-17-usc-101","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 101 — Definitions (work made for hire)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/101"},{"id":"stat-17-usc-201","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 201","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/201"}],"title":"No IP-ownership clause detected"},{"description":"Neither 'indemnify' nor 'hold harmless' appears in the document.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no indemnification language)"},"explanation":"Most commercial contracts allocate risk through an indemnification clause. The absence leaves the parties to default tort and contract law for any third-party claims.","id":"RISK-001-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No indemnification clause detected"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a limitation-of-liability clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no LoL clause)"},"explanation":"Without a limitation-of-liability clause, exposure is bounded only by what the parties can prove in damages. Most commercial contracts cap liability.","id":"RISK-005-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No limitation-of-liability clause detected"},{"description":"Used but not defined: Personal Information.","document_position":424,"excerpt":{"end_offset":444,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":424,"text":"Personal Information"},"explanation":"Title-Case phrases in a contract usually signal a defined term. When they aren't defined, readers must guess at the intended meaning. Either define them or use lowercase if the term is intended in its ordinary sense.","id":"STRUCT-006-s1-424","recommendation":"Add a definition for each genuinely defined term, or change the casing if the phrase is being used in its ordinary sense.","rule_id":"STRUCT-006","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Undefined Title-Case terms: 1"},{"description":"The contract does not state a path to terminate for material breach.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no for-cause termination)"},"explanation":"Without a for-cause termination path, parties must rely on common-law material-breach doctrines, which are jurisdiction-dependent.","id":"TERM-002-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No termination-for-cause clause detected"},{"description":"No clause was found prohibiting combining personal information with other data sources.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 1798.140(ag)(1)(D) restricts combining the personal information with data from other sources.","id":"USDPA-004-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Service Provider shall not combine personal information received from Business with personal information received from any other source, except as permitted by 11 CCR § 7050(c).'","rule_id":"USDPA-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-140-ag-1-d-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.140(ag)(1)(D)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA no-combining restriction missing"},{"description":"No clause was found specifically addressing sensitive personal information.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"CCPA / CPRA, CPA, CTDPA define sensitive personal information / sensitive data and impose heightened obligations.","id":"USDPA-022-s1-0","recommendation":"Add a 'Sensitive Personal Information' clause describing categories handled and SPI-specific safeguards.","rule_id":"USDPA-022","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-121","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.121","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"Sensitive personal information handling not addressed"},{"description":"No reference to data minimization was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Several state privacy statutes incorporate a data-minimization principle requiring collection of only what is reasonably necessary.","id":"USDPA-024-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Personal data collected and processed shall be limited to what is reasonably necessary and proportionate to the disclosed purpose.'","rule_id":"USDPA-024","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-100-c-multi-state-minimization","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.100(c) / Multi-state minimization","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"Data-minimization principle not referenced"},{"description":"The document does not state where disputes must be brought.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no venue clause)"},"explanation":"Without a venue clause, default venue rules apply (in federal court, 28 U.S.C. § 1391). A clear forum-selection clause avoids ambiguity.","id":"CHOICE-003-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-28-usc-1391","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"28 U.S.C. § 1391 (venue generally)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/28/1391"}],"title":"No venue / forum clause detected"},{"description":"Service Provider shall process Personal Information solely for the Business Purpose and shall not process Personal Infor | Service Provider hereby certifies that it understands and shall comply with the following prohibitions: (a) Service Prov | 140(al) and shall receive no monetary or other valuable consideration for selling Personal Information; (b) Service Prov | 140(al) and shall receive no monetary or other valuable consideration for selling Personal Information; (b) Service Prov","document_position":1405,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1566,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1405,"text":"Service Provider shall process Personal Information solely for the Business Purpose and shall not process Personal Information for any other commercial purpose."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-1405","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 6"},{"description":"The following defined terms are never used outside their definition: CCPA/CPRA.","document_position":618,"excerpt":{"end_offset":631,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":618,"text":"CCPA/CPRA"},"explanation":"Defined terms that are not used downstream may be inherited from a template and obsolete. They clutter the contract and can confuse readers; either delete them or use them where intended.","id":"STRUCT-005-s1-618","recommendation":"Review each unused term and either delete it or wire it into the relevant clause.","rule_id":"STRUCT-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Defined terms with no uses: 1"}],"playbook_id":"dpa-ccpa-service-provider","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to dpa-ccpa-service-provider","result_hash":"8b019468b37fda8eb8c6614d0935d0ef4c77b3ad922186f68ef6af33d5fcb360","source_file":{"name":"dpa-ccpa-service-provider-missing-no-combining-restriction-fail.txt","sha256":"c7fa7c14c894c1349c9b06052879585fd4b4b85ee6ec742f797824851e1cd6a7","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}